# Internal dev / debug folders
debug/
# docs/ is mostly private (research notes etc) — exclude its contents
# directly so the negation below can still let docs/screenshots/ through.
# (Negating inside a fully-excluded directory doesn't work; you must
# leave the directory itself trackable.)
docs/*
!docs/screenshots/
!docs/screenshots/**
bridge_templates/

# Misc dev scripts not part of the runtime project
apply_grass_pattern.py
extract_bridge_templates.py
preprocess.py
generate.js
split_noncontiguous_items.py
# Stale older root-level server (replaced by backend/server.js)
/server.js
# Stale older static folder (replaced by little_town/public/)
/public/
# Large unused tile pack
SERENE_VILLAGE_REVAMPED/

# Debug output from generator / tile-identification scripts
preview_map.png
tile_reference.png
samp_*.png
sample_*.png
tiles_strip_*.png
Trace-*.json

# Licensed LimeZu Modern Interiors / Exteriors assets — NEVER COMMIT.
# Buy your own copy at https://limezu.itch.io/ and place the PNGs
# back where the README's "Building your own map" section describes.
# We commit only the Tiled .tmx + .tsx authoring files (which
# reference these PNGs by relative path) and the exported map JSON.
# Top-level raw asset library (leading slash = root only — must not
# also ignore little_town/public/assets/tilemaps/ which holds the map JSON):
/assets/
# Tileset slices copied into the served public folder:
little_town/public/assets/tilesets/*.png
# LimeZu Modern Interiors character generator copies:
little_town/public/assets/characters/**/*.png
little_town/public/assets/character_builder/**/*.png
little_town/public/assets/character_builder/**/manifest.json
little_town/public/assets/character_builder/Spritesheet_animations_GUIDE.png
little_town/public/assets/Modern_Interiors/
# Debug trace images:
little_town/public/assets/trace/
# Tuxemon-town tutorial sample (unused — was Phaser learning-material):
little_town/public/assets/tilemaps/tuxemon-town.*
